17 August 2016The Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi, will host a Media Transformation, Accountability and Diversity Colloquium on the 25th and the 26th of August 2016 at Freedom Park, Pretoria. We take stock of the transformation that has occurred in this industry, to ensure that the ownership of these influential media assets reflects our diversity, said Muthambi.The Colloquium aims to bring together a broad range of stakeholders that will contribute to a meaningful debate on media transformation, accountability and diversity priorities in our country. Various stakeholders ranging from NGOs (non-governmental organisations), government departments, advocacy forums, media houses, academia, civil society and other key role players are set to attend. Untransformed media is unable to comprehensively demonstrate the plurality of voices in our societies diversity in content, added Muthambi Members of the media are invited to attend the Colloquium as follows:Date: 25th and 26th August 2016 Time: 09h00 Venue: Freedom Park, Koch St &amp; 7th Ave, Salvokop, Pretoria (GPS coordinates: -25.767000, 28.188800)RSVP: Ms Noni Moimane noni@gcis.gov.za (076 964 9610)Enquiries: Mr Mish Molakeng Cell: 082 469 3997 E-mail: mishack@doc.gov.zaIssued by Department of Communications